he should have preferred l’impair and accommodated with nine syllables what Marvell fits into eight. In the lines:

And, quite regardless of my smart,

Left me his fawn but took his heart



which come out as:

Et se moquant bien de ma douleur

Me laissa son faon, mais pris son coeur



one regrets that the translator, even with the help of an ampler prosodie womb, did not manage to fold in the long legs of her French fawn, and render “quite regardless of” by “sans le moindre égard pour